  <p>Suspects everyone as worthy of suspicion.</p>
  <p>It's only the system that nudges us to unproductive and distructive behaviour.</p>
  <p>No one person was responsible for creating it, and no one person can change it.</p>
  <p>This spiral, people get despereate.</p>
  <p>The natural world constantly getting eaten up.</p>
  <h3>The Result</h3>
  <p>It reduces us to cogs in a machine and with an entrenched collective scarcity mentality.</p>
  <p>Resources that could have gone to providing sheldering us, are used to box us in.</p>
  <p>We don't have to be so hard on each other, we don't have to make little children sit still at desks, and or make welfare recipients apply for jobs, and the world won't fall apart.</p>
  <p>We have a system that instills and promotes bad habits. (Greber said this) we need to opposite.</p>
